notesStmt.note: This conversation involves a Maltese family (S1, S2, S4) and a Serbian student (S3). They have been driving around in a car to show the foreign student some sights in Malta. Then they return to the family's home, where the daughter of the family (S4) prepares to go out. In the meantime, S3 talks to S1 and S2 in the living room and in the kitchen, while she waits for S4. Once S4 is ready, S3 and S4 drive to a third girl's house (S5) to pick her up and continue to another friend's house where they are going to spend the evening. On the way, S4 asks S6 and S7 for directions in Maltese.

equipment.p: Portable minidisc recorder with electret condenser stereo microphone
